Two people were killed and two more injured when a rollercoaster carriage derailed at a theme park in Mexico, authorities have said. Early reports suggest a mechanical problem caused the carriage to become detatched from the ride and fall some 10 metres to the ground, the public prosecutor said in a statement. READ ALSO: 2019 UTME: Over 100,000 candidates got varsity admission – JAMB It is believed the two men died as a result of head injuries, it added, while two women were taken to the hospital — one of them in a serious condition. The accident happened at La Feria amusement park in the capital Mexico City on Saturday. In a Twitter post, the theme park said it “deeply regrets the terrible accident” and it has launched an investigation into the incident. (AFP)